The paper deals with uncertainty estimation in machine learning systems, which is a common topic in the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the reliability of these systems under adversarial conditions, which falls under the sub-field of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The two real-world problems used for validation, question answering and medical diagnosis from genomic data, are both related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computational biology (cs.SI), respectively.
